    rental_id UUID PRIMARY KEY, 
    rental_start_date TIMESTAMP, 
    return_date TIMESTAMP, 
    rental_duration INTERVAL, 
    total_cost DECIMAL 
)

CREATE TABLE transaction (
  transaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  rental_start_date DATE,
  return_date DATE,
  rental_duration INT,
  total_cost DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE rental_transactions (
    rental_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    rental_start_date TIMESTAMP,
    return_date TIMESTAMP,
    rental_duration INTERVAL,
    total_cost DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE rental_transactions (
    transaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    rental_start_date DATE,
    return_date DATE,
    rental_duration INT,
    total_cost DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE rental_details (
    transaction_id INT,
    customer_id INT,
    item_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (transaction_id) REFERENCES rental_transactions(transaction_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (item_id) REFERENCES rental_items(item_id)
);

CREATE TABLE rental_transactions (
  transaction_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  rental_start_date DATE,
  return_date DATE,
  rental_duration INTERVAL,
  total_cost DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE customers (
  customer_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_name VARCHAR(255),
  customer_email VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE rental_items (
  item_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  item_name VARCHAR(255),
  item_description TEXT,
  rental_price DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE rental_history (
  rental_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  transaction_id INT,
  item_id INT,
  rental_date DATE,
  returned_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE rental_locations (
  location_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  location_name VARCHAR(255),
  location_address TEXT
)
